In a #small pot{}, combine @white rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to use in Step 5.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and thinly slice @button mushrooms{8%ounce}.

> Skip slicing mushrooms if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, scallion whites, @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon}, 1 tsp @sugar{4%teaspoon}, and ¼ tsp @salt{}. Microwave for ~{45%seconds}. Set aside to pickle, tossing occasionally.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sriracha sauce{1%teaspoon}, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, half the @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, and @sugar{1%TBSP}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{5%teaspoon} in a medium, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Stir in 2 tsp sauce, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Turn off heat; transfer mushrooms to one side of a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat another drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @spinach{5%ounce} and cook, stirring, until wilted, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in remaining sesame oil. Transfer spinach to empty side of plate with mushrooms; wipe out pan.

Rinse shrimp under cold water. Pat @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a separate plate. Wipe out pan.

> Top crispy rice with shrimp or chicken along with mushrooms, spinach, and pickled carrots.

Once rice is done, heat a large drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over high heat. Once oil is very hot and almost smoking, add cooked rice; spread out in an even layer. Cook, undisturbed, until a crust forms on the bottom of rice, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> Oil may splatter a bit—be careful!

Remove pan from heat.

In pan, top crispy rice with mushrooms, spinach, and pickled carrots (draining first) in separate sections.

Drizzle everything with remaining sauce and garnish with scallion greens and @crispy fried onions{1%unit}. Serve directly from pan.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.